rComments: Took Biomedical Ethics, she's an amazing prof! Always there to answer questions before and after class, as well as during office hours. Her lectures are very engaging. Some people took the course for an easy A which is why many of them didn't like it. I enjoyed her course, as she was a great teacher. Really easy to have conversations with her.

She is very straightforward and strong about her opinions. I took PHLB09 - Bioethics during my first year. As long as you are familiar with cases in the textbook, you will be good for the midterm and final. Yes, it is textbook heavy. Lots of reading, but most of it is repetitive.

Midterm was really easy, but one hour wasn't enough time to answer all the questions to the quality that she wanted. Essays were marked hard. Tutorial participation and attendance are very important as it accounts for 20% of final grade.

Lectures were informative, but consisted of reading off her PowerPoint (which she posted online). Exams were heavy--not hard per se, but she did not give enough time to answer all the questions to the extent that she wanted. Tough, but fair on essays.
